  "text": "B Cell-Derived IL-10 Inhibits Immunity to Salmonella We have previously found that in EAE, the suppressive function of B cells on T cell-mediated immunity depends on both MyD88 and IL-10 [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . We therefore asked whether B cells counterregulate cellular mechanisms of protective immunity via IL-10 during Salmonella infection.",
